    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="309"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8–1744</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-21">August 21,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I enclose a copy of a letter dated August 17, 1944 from Admiral Leahy,<note
                        n="87" xml:id="d309fn87">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_540">p. 540</ref>.</note>
                    transmitting a telegram of July 10, 1944 from S.H.A.E.F. recommending the
                    issuance at the proper moment of simultaneous orders of the day to the troops
                    under the command of Marshal Stalin and Generals Eisenhower and Wilson to the
                    effect that the final battle has begun and that “all is up” for Germany.</p>
                <p>I see no objection to this proposal from the political point of view and consider
                    it primarily a military matter. If you approve the proposal, you will no doubt
                    wish to take it up with Churchill and Stalin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
